# Keep documentation up to date

When you change this repository, treat **README.md** and **docs/** as part of the
deliverable—not optional follow-up work.

## When to update

Update docs in the **same change** (same PR / commit series) when you modify:

- User-visible behavior (keys, CLI args, panel semantics, mouse, status bar)
- Features or limitations (syntax support, diff model, file browser)
- Project structure (new crates, moved modules, renamed binaries)
- Toolchain or tasks (`pixi.toml`, Rust version, build/test/install commands)
- Packaging (`recipe/`, conda/pixi global install paths)
- Architecture or engineering trade-offs (new dependencies, data flow, caching)

If the change is purely internal with **zero** observable or operational impact,
docs updates are optional—but still skim README and the relevant `docs/*.md` file
for stale wording.

## What to update

| Change type | Primary doc | Also check |
|-------------|-------------|------------|
| Install / usage / shortcuts | `README.md` | `docs/goals-and-limitations.md` if scope shifts |
| Libraries, Pixi tasks, packaging | `docs/tech-stack.md` | `README.md` (Quick start, Testing, Conda) |
| Modules, data flow, crates | `docs/architecture.md` | `README.md` (Project structure) |
| Design rationale / trade-offs | `docs/engineering-decisions.md` | `docs/goals-and-limitations.md` |
| Scope, non-goals, known limits | `docs/goals-and-limitations.md` | `README.md` Features table |
| New doc pages | `docs/README.md` index table | Cross-links from related pages |

Also keep **AGENTS.md** aligned when Cloud-agent or Pixi workflow instructions
change (it duplicates some build/run facts agents rely on).

## How to update

1. Make the code change first; then edit docs to match **current** behavior—do
   not document planned or aspirational features.
2. Prefer updating the **most specific** doc; avoid duplicating long passages
   across files. README stays user-facing; `docs/` holds depth.
3. Use the same commands that work in this repo (`pixi run …`, not bare `cargo`
   unless explicitly documenting the fallback).
4. If you remove or reverse a decision, delete or revise the old rationale in
   `docs/engineering-decisions.md`—do not leave contradictions.
5. After substantive doc edits, verify facts against `pixi.toml`, `Cargo.toml`,
   and source (especially key bindings in `app.rs` and diff model in `diff.rs`).

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] README.md still accurate for install, features, and key bindings
- [ ] Relevant `docs/*.md` pages updated (not only the index)
- [ ] No conflicting statements between README, docs, and AGENTS.md
- [ ] New limitations or non-goals noted in `docs/goals-and-limitations.md`
